name: New York earthquake
summary: On August 24, 2023, a 4.8 magnitude earthquake struck the New York City area, causing widespread shaking from New York to Ontario and even Quebec. The earthquake was felt during a United Nations Security Council meeting, causing the meeting to be briefly interrupted. While the earthquake did not cause any major damage, it did raise concerns about potential seismic activity in the region. Social media platforms, such as Twitter, were flooded with videos, photos, and eyewitness accounts of the earthquake, with the hashtag "#NYCEarthquake" trending.

name: When is daylight savings
summary: Daylight Saving Time (DST) is a practice of advancing clocks during spring and summer months to make better use of daylight hours. In 2024, DST will start in the United States on March 10th and end on November 3rd. Some states, such as Arizona and Hawaii, do not observe DST. DST can have benefits, such as reduced energy consumption and increased outdoor recreation time, but it has also been criticized for its potential impact on sleep patterns and other health concerns. In some countries, including Greece and Israel, DST is in effect for a portion of the year. Watch manufacturers are also developing timepieces that can automatically adjust to DST changes, addressing the potential inconvenience of having to manually adjust clocks. Additionally, there are ongoing debates about the effectiveness and necessity of DST, with some advocating for its discontinuation or modification.

summary: On April 8, 2024, a total solar eclipse will occur, visible in Prince Edward County.
